Files:
- docs/content/docs/reference/configuration.mdx (fix example config and settings prose)

Context:
The settings resolver (platform/mcp-server/src/settings-resolver.ts line 68-76) requires url-type settings to be a Record<string,string> (instance name → URL map), NOT a plain string. The code checks: `if (typeof rawValue !== 'object' || rawValue === null || Array.isArray(rawValue)) { log.warn(...'expected a Record<string, string>, got...' — skipping) }`. If a user follows the current example and puts a plain string, the setting is silently skipped with a warning.

The current broken example config (around line 82-110):
```json
"settings": {
  "jira": {
    "instanceUrl": "https://mycompany.atlassian.net"
  }
}
```

Changes:
1. Update the example config to show the correct format:
```json
"settings": {
  "jira": {
    "instanceUrl": { "prod": "https://mycompany.atlassian.net" }
  }
}
```

2. Around line 224, the existing prose says: 'url-type settings are stored as `Record<string, string>` maps from instance name to URL, enabling plugins that work across multiple user-specific instances without hardcoded URL patterns.' This prose is correct — keep it.

3. Update `lastUpdated` frontmatter to `2026-04-15`.

Constraints:
